metadata.executive_summary: The Company reported strong performance in FY25 Q4, with net sales reaching $159.9 billion and adjusted operating income of $7.1 billion. Total revenues increased to $182.6 billion, reflecting a 5.3% growth in constant currency. The adjusted EPS was $0.60, demonstrating resilience despite challenges in the market. The gross profit rate improved to 23.9%, supported by effective inventory management and a favorable business mix.
